'========================================================================
' Outlook Email Automation Module
' Author: D. Hyres
' March, 2026
'========================================================================
' Purpose:
'   - Automatically organizes incoming Outlook emails by sender or subject
'     into specified folders.
'   - Logs moved emails and sends a daily summary email.
'
' How it works:
'   1. This module defines rules (sender and subject) and the main processing
'      routines to move emails and log them.
'   2. ThisOutlookSession contains event handlers that call ProcessMail
'      when new mail arrives and start the daily summary timer when Outlook starts.
'   3. Daily summary is sent using a timer loop (avoids Application.OnTime issues).
'
' Usage / Notes:
'   - Place this code in a **standard module** (e.g., modEmailAutomation).
'   - Ensure macros are enabled in Outlook.
'   - Configure sender-based rules in InitializeRules().
'   - Optional: Configure subject-based rules similarly.
'   - SetupDailyTask allows configuring the summary send time.
'   - Debug.Print statements can be viewed in the Immediate Window (Ctrl+G).
'   - Nested folders are supported via "\" in folder paths.
'========================================================================
'========================================================================
'========================================================================

Option Explicit


'=============================
' Global Variables
'=============================
Public SenderRules As Variant       ' Array storing rules based on sender email addresses
Public SubjectRules As Variant      ' Array storing rules based on email subjects (currently placeholder)
Public MovedEmails As Collection    ' Collection to log all emails that were moved during the day

'=============================
' Initialize Email Rules
'=============================
